  "articleSummary": "This technical guide argues for a pragmatic, layered approach to securing developer workstations by reducing the \"blast radius\" of compromised processes. The author advocates for a defense-in-depth strategy focusing on four pillars: environment isolation via Dev Containers, secure secret handling (moving away from plaintext `.env` files), threat detection, and egress control. Written in a practical, opinionated, and developer-centric tone, the article uses the \"blast radius\" metaphor to frame security as a matter of limiting the inheritance of user permissions. It specifically highlights the risks of over-broad directory mounting and the emerging security challenges posed by AI coding agents.",
